enment thought and beyond, Pietz reveals the violent emergence of a foundational concept for modern theories of value, belief, desire, and difference. This book cements Pietz’s legacy of engaging questions about material culture, object agency, merchant capitalism, and spiritual power, and introduces a powerful theorist to a new generation of thinkers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFetishismxHistory. 0aFetishismxPhilosophy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  apower, spirituality, religion, merchant capitalism, object agency, material culture, difference, desire, belief, value, enlightenment, west africa, colonization, portugal, human life, money, blood sacrifice, marx, fetishism, ritual, rite, ceremony, nonfiction, anthropology, folklore, sociology, thing theory, animism, philosophy, colonialism, sovereignty, independence.1 aGeroulanos, Stefanos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeroulanos, Stefanos, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKafka, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKafka, Ben, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPellizzi, Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPellizzi, Francesco, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyter